description: Flash Gordon's classic era in comic books returns in a new archival collection from Dark Horse! Join the handsome and fearless Flash, his clever and capable companion Dale Arden, and eccentric scientist Dr. Zarkov as they face peril and danger in the wild landscapes of the planet Mongo and go head to head with the villainous despot Ming the Merciless! This archival collection, reprinting seven complete comics originally published from 1947 through 1953, makes a fine addition to any comics library. Ray guns, spaceships, and Silver Age storytelling -- it's all here and it's all action!

T.H.U.N.D.E.R. AGENTS doesn't let up on the throttle for a second as the team's assault on the Spider compound to rescue a captured teammate continues! Plus, special guest artist ChrisCross (FIRESTORM) illustrates a story spotlighting the backstory of doomed speedster Lightning!
name: Live Fast, Die Young

description: Cyril and Beryl have the fight of their lives on their hands when Shakespeare's most evil monarch, Richard III, returns! And he's brought with him a cloned army of all the worst Kings of England, intent on taking back the country through the use of social networking! Yes, that's the plot!
name: For Six: Part Three

description:
Doc's adventure in the war-torn Middle East takes a nasty turn when he realizes that the people who sent him into the Zone don't necessarily want him coming back out. Meanwhile, the threat he came to neutralize is not what it seems!

And in the JUSTICE, INC. co-feature, there's nothing standing between Smitty and his quarry, the murdering scum he plans to pay back in kind – but what will become of him if he breaks Benson's cardinal rule? "Murder and Vengeance" concludes here!
name: Man of Fire; Murder And Vengeance Part Four: Final Judgment

description: Ancient evil never dies... It waits on the other side of the curtain for humanity to stumble. Faro Korbit is an immortal mystic, sole defender against a Lovecraftian menace. As the forces of evil gather in the Nevada desert, Faro recruits an odd assortment of allies: a cocktail waitress, a grand prix driver, and a dancer. Unless they succeed, humanity will be scoured from the earth like a billiard ball in a clothes washer.

The body count starts to rise as De Monique and her demon horde prepare for the Great Old One's return. De Monique turns the Las Vegas Grand Prix into an abbatoir, saving her most exquisite torture for the losing driver. Faro's new pal Audrey turns out to be an action babe. Not a fake action babe. A real action babe!

As the army of darkness gathers in the Nevada desert, the demon Klaq once again strides the Earth, preparing for the return of the Great Old One. Klaq's shock troops, the animated corpses of murderers, have seized Audrey and placed her in the heart of a mechanical man to be sacrificed at the moment of nuclear detonation. Faro, Race, and Blue seemingly don't stand a chance against the combined might of Klaq and the National Guard. But they're going to give it one hell of a shot!
Collects the unfinished Faro Korbit mini-series (#1-3) and issue #4 the unpublished issue.
name: Volume 1

description: Reena has few friends and finds it difficult to interact with her peers. As she struggles with her problems her father, Koss, relives the brutal past which resulted in the death of Reena’s mother. The resultant fury which Koss vents changes the balance of power and forges a powerful alliance. Reena’s destiny will determine the fate of her people.
name: The Rescue

description: Reena is challenged and fights an older boy. The fight is brutally quick and Reena storms away in anger. As a result of this she makes an astonishing discovery far from home. Upon her return she hears that a fearsome enemy has been seen, threatening the peace that the Phoenix and Lion tribes have brought to the area.

Reena re-enters the new world that she has discovered, which she does in secret. She immerses herself in the ancient writings, determined to decipher their meaning which could shed light on the past and her ancestors. Back home preparations are being made to counter a serious and fearsome threat, for The Leopard tribe has finally arrived!

The powerful Leopard army appears in force at the walls of Rell. The Leopard Chieftain, Merek, gives Koss an ultimatum: Peace or War. He then makes another demand which stuns the Phoenix Chieftain, as he knows that to reject it will mean war and certain defeat. The survival of the entire region rests on Koss and his decision.

The Leopard tribe finally leaves and a fragile peace exists, based on promises forced upon the Phoenix tribe. As time passes it seems that peace is assured, until one day the Leopards appear unannounced again. This time there is an unwelcome addition to their ranks. He is the brutal son of their Chieftain, and he has come to meet his future bride, Reena!

Koss and Reena take time out to visit their allies, the Lion tribe. Their problems are temporarily forgotten as they re-acquaint themselves with old friends. Reena meets an old friend who has transformed himself into an accomplished warrior, and the chemistry between them is clear! But Koss is not there just to relax; he is there to plan for war!

Reena’s torment continues as she tries to come to terms with the bleak and brutal future planned against her wishes. She finds solace in her secret discovery and immerses herself in studying the past. Meanwhile, the brutal Leopard tribe invite her Father to the newly built fortress, a seemingly ideal opportunity for the Leopards’ to rid themselves of their rival.

The Phoenix have been invited to the lair of the Leopards. Koss suspects a trap but goes despite his fears. What he sees upon their arrival stuns him, and confirms that the power has now shifted to the dreaded Leopards. Unfortunately for Koss the surprises don’t end there, for while he is visiting, a mistake from his past comes back to haunt him.

The gruesome death of a Phoenix warrior whilst on a “friendly” visit to the gigantic fortress of the Leopard tribe confirms Koss’ fears for the future. The fragile peace is soon shattered as Reena challenges her betrothed in defense of a friend, which leads to a critical moment in the relationship between the two tribes.

Koss orders his people to prepare the compound for an attack by the Leopard tribe. Reena heads back to the cavern where she finally deciphers the mysterious runes. She hurries back to Rell to warn her people of the stunning revelations. Can she prevent the Phoenix tribe’s tragic history from repeating itself?

The Phoenix tribe is attacked by their ferocious enemy who will stop at nothing to wipe them out. Koss and his people battle bravely against the odds, and against warriors who seemingly cannot be killed. What forces are at play here? Have the Phoenix finally met their match?

The FINALE: Reena flees for her life from the hellish scene that was Rell, pursued by her worst nightmare. There is only one place to go to escape; The Forbidden Forest! Reena will have to endure trials that would test the bravest warrior if she is to find the answers that she has for so long been seeking.

Collects The Lexian Chronicles: Full Circle #1-5.

The once peaceful region of Alemar is threatened by the re-emergence of a powerful tribe hell-bent on settling in the area. Amidst the turmoil that their arrival has caused, Reena has made an incredible discovery which throws a new light upon the history of her tribe and the disasters that befell them. Reena struggles with the responsibilities that have been forced upon her, and seeks comfort in her amazing and secret find.
name: TPB

description:
Collects The Lexian Chronicles: Full Circle #6-12.

Oats Reena and the Phoenix tribe continue to struggle with the consequences surrounding the re-emergence of the dreaded Leopard tribe. As Reena struggles to come to terms with her betrothal to the Leopard heir she studies the ancient runes in secret, in an attempt to unravel the mysteries surrounding her ancestors. The key to the Phoenix tribe's future could be held in the mysteries of the past, and Reena is determined to find out what they are.
name: TPB

description: Tony Stark's worst fears are realized when stolen Iron Man technology is used for ethnic cleansing in a civil war-ravaged land. When he defies U.S. government orders to confront the armored assassins himself, Stark sets off an international conflagration that threatens his friends, his company, and his very life -- and sets him on a collision course with China and Russia, and their champions, Radioactive Man, Titanium Man and the Crimson Dynamo! Guest-stars galore! Collecting IRON MAN LEGACY #1-5 and IRON MAN: HARD RAIN.
name: Iron Man: War of the Iron Men

volume.name: Iron Man: War of the Iron Men

description: Collects Monster Club Volume 1 issues #1-5.
name: trade

description: Collects Monster Club Volume 1 issues #6-9.
name: trade

description: To save the very universe, Thor and the Warriors Three travel through time to stop the deadly Time Twisters! Then, it's off to Costa Verde to face the new threat of Firelord-but when Thor gets mind-controlled, only Jane Foster can save the day! And when Mangog storms the gates of Asgard, Thor must rescue his father Odin from Hela herself! Witness the God of Thunder in some of his earliest battles! Featuring the threats of Ulik, Zarrko the Tomorrow Man and more! Collecting THOR (1962) #242-253.
name: Thor: If Asgard Should Perish

description: So what is all the talk about? Monster Club has been on the lips of comic fans around the world. Now jump on with the first issue of the next series as Mia and her team embark on yet another monster-mashing mission, this time with a new member!
name: A New Beginning

volume.name: The Black Coat: "...Or Give Me Death"

description: Psychological horror in the vein of The Twilight Zone and Tales From the Crypt has returned! In these first three tales of terror, a one night stand becomes a conspiracy of Lovecraftian proportions; a man stranded at sea with his pregnant wife considers a ghoulish pact for survival; and a glimpse into Hell reveals Lucifer's plan to use the seven deadly sins to begin the Armageddon!

Sheriff Clark and Deputy Jefferson are about to embark on the biggest misadventure of their lives. The Creatures from the Sky have arrived...and they're hungry.

This issue - Clark & Jefferson have made it to Fort Corman only to find the remaining people fighting for their lives against the aliens.

Sheriff Clark and Deputy Jefferson are about to embark on the biggest misadventure of their lives. The Creatures from the Sky have arrived...and they're hungry.

This issue - Clark & Jefferson are making their last stand with the remaining people at the Fort as the aliens continue their attack.

Sheriff Clark and Deputy Jefferson are about to embark on the biggest misadventure of their lives. The Creatures from the Sky have arrived...and they're hungry.

This issue - Clark & Jefferson and the remaining survivors have made it onto the alien ship and figured out a way to destroy it. The only problem is that none of them may make it off of the ship alive as the mini series wraps up with a bang.

Three stories written by Ray Bradbury and illustrated by several artists. "It Burns Me Up" -- a noir sort of story narrated by a dead man -- was adapted as a comic by Harvey Kurtzman and Matt Wagner, lettered by Tim Sale. "Touched with Fire" -- when the temperature rises, so do violent crimes -- was adapted by Sean Phillips and lettered by Willie Schubert. "The Black Ferris" -- the short story that later became Something Wicked This Way Comes -- was adapted by Jack Davis, with Heather Brown as colorist. Introduction by Ray Bradbury.
name: Horror

description: As thousands of anti-war protesters converge on Washington D.C. in the Spring of 1968, the violence and turbulence of the time is about to explode into an unprecedented orgy of murder never before seen on American soil. Although the media conveniently explained the tales of the dead rising to kill the living as the work of militants and anti-Vietnam War radicals, something insidious is indeed lurking in the shadows of the Nation's capitol, and their grip on the country is about to make itself known. But with their troop numbers spread impossibly thin from both war-time service and riot control, the National Guard know that one misstep in dealing with the protesters could set off a fatal firestorm of violence during this most emotional time... And they will be woefully unprepared to defend the city from the flesh-hungry army of the undead about to descend upon them all.
name: 2 (of 5)

description:
The last of Adeline Pratt's humanity might finally be beat out of her as the few survivors left in her family begin to turn on each other. Can it really be the humans are just as evil as the Crossed? The best laid plans fall apart and all bets are off as their Mother returns - now as a Crossed and looking to turn her children as well. Imagine, for a moment, the worst crimes against humanity. Picture the cruelest affronts to decency. Conjure your darkest nightmares... and then realize it could all be so much worse.

When civilization crumbles in one terrifying moment; when people are gleefully breaking into unthinkable acts of violence all around you; when everyone you love has died screaming in agony: What do you do? There is no help. There is no hope. There is no escape. There are only the Crossed.

The race for the Sol Emerald continues, and things are getting heated! Can Team Rose and Team Dark settle down long enough to track down a thieving trio of hooligans? And when a surprise fourth team joins the fray, will it make things better - or worse?
name: Treasure Team Tango, Part Three: The Llevada
